Databricks is built on top of Apache Spark, but it adds a lot of functionality on top of the Spark engine to make it easier to use in enterprise environments. Let me break it down clearly:

Managed Spark Clusters – Auto-provisioning, scaling, and optimized configuration.

Databricks Runtime – Optimized Spark engine with pre-installed libraries.

Delta Lake – ACID-compliant storage, schema enforcement, time travel.

Interactive Notebooks – Multi-language, collaboration, visualizations.

Jobs & Workflows – Scheduling, automation, monitoring pipelines.

Security & Governance – RBAC, encryption, audit logging.

Performance Optimizations – AQE, Z-Ordering, partitioning, caching.

ML & AI Integration – MLflow, MLlib, TensorFlow, PyTorch.

SQL Analytics & BI Integration – Dashboards, BI connectors.

Streaming & Real-time Processing – Structured Streaming + Delta Lake.

